President William Ruto together with Cabinet Secretaries marked day three of the CSs retreat in Nanyuki. Other government officials like Principal Secretaries, advisers and governors were also present at the retreat. "Our singular focus is working together to deliver services to Kenyans. The ambition of our development agenda demands a seamless collaboration with the Legislature and county governments," RutoÂ  said. The agenda of the retreat is to adopt the administration's economic transformation plan based on priorities such as food security and job creation. The president urged the CSs to commit to building a strong partnership to help achieve the desires of the people. The four-day retreat started on January 5 and will end on January 8.